<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[94,718,410,691]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[94,205,410,435]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Remarks:</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Pic, M." box="[212,322,410,435]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="90 - 93" refId="ref20217" refString="Pic, M. 1906. Noms nouveaux et diagnoses de &quot; Cantharini &quot; (Telephorides) europeens et exotiques. L'Echange, Revue Linneenne, 22 (264): 90 - 93." type="journal article" year="1906">Pic (1906)</bibRefCitation>
described this species from an unspecified number of males from “Cayenne”. We found 
<specimenCount box="[94,216,474,499]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="male">three male</specimenCount>
specimens at MNHN and NHMB, all with different locality data, which we here consider part of the original type series. This includes a specimen at NHMB cited as a non-type by 
<bibRefCitation author="Constantin, R." box="[359,574,570,595]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="7 - 29" refId="ref19688" refString="Constantin, R. 2010 a. A contribution to knowledge of the Cantharidae (Coleoptera, Elateroidea) in Ecuador and French Guiana. Entomologica Basiliensia et Collectionis Frey, 32: 7 - 29." type="journal article" year="2010">Constantin (2010a)</bibRefCitation>
, which however bears a “cotype” label in Pic’s handwriting. The male 
<typeStatus box="[94,182,634,659]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">syntype</typeStatus>
at MNHN, in Pic’s own collection, is here designated as the 
<typeStatus box="[236,344,666,691]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">lectotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
